column1: Title: Teen Birth Rate per 1,000 Population Ages 15-19 | KFF
Data are by place of residence. Population includes females 15-19 years old.

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), [National Vital Statistics Reports (NVSR), Vol. 64, No. 12: Births: Final Data for 2014](http://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/nvsr/nvsr64/nvsr64_12.pdf), December 23, 2015.
1. US teen birth rate excludes data from the territories.
